N1  - Funding text 1: Exhibit 1: The Video Game Project, “US-Russia Cultural Dialogue.” This digital instructional program takes the form of an interactive video game which allows English language learners exposure to colloquial and formal registers of American English in a variety of culturally-relevant contexts. The video game was designed during a year-long grant project sponsored by the U.S. Department of State’s U.S.-Russia Peer-to-Peer Dialogue Program. The project was titled, “Getting Closer: A Cross-Cultural U.S.-Russian Project Focusing on Teaching Foreign Languages to U.S. students and Blind/Visually Impaired Students in Russia.” This video game allowed students at the University of Central Florida to bring immersive experience in English language and American culture with them as they traveled to St. Petersburg, Russia, where it was presented for EFL use at a school for the blind and visually impaired. It is predicted that the video game will be viewed as a useful and innovative tool for EFL classrooms in blind and visually impaired schools and elsewhere in Russia, as it achieves exposure to written and spoken American English conducted by native speakers. This includes exposure to variant forms of regional colloquial English, as well as light exposure to the presence of Spanish language as an important reminder of American cultural diversity.
